<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-14T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4478: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-14T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 14, 1919,
                                        4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>1965. Following from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName>: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“May 13, 1 p.m. Russian Ambassador has informed me that
                                        <persName>Ivanoff-Rinoff</persName> has been recalled by the
                                        <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> Government,
                                    claims, being in my opinion a victory for general fusion [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] which might form one of the grounds
                                    for recognition of the Omsk Government.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>You will recall that <persName>Ivanoff-Rinoff</persName> was the Russian
                            Commander in Eastern Siberia who has been responsible for arbitrary and
                            reactionary policies which have been so much complained of by American
                            representatives and liberal Russians.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>